---
import Layout from '../layouts/BlogPost.astro';
---

<Layout
	title="About Me""
	pubDate={new Date('June 26 2026')}
>
<section>

	<p>
		Hi, I&apos;m Austin Heath.
	</p>
	<p>
		I&apos;m a Senior Cloud Security Consultant at CrowdStrike with a background in
		Incident Response and Digital Forensics. Throughout my career, I&apos;ve helped
		investigate and respond to complex security incidents across enterprise environments,
		with previous experience at both CrowdStrike and Mandiant (Google).
	</p>
	<p>
		HeathBarSec is where I document my research into cloud security, detection engineering,
		incident response, and AI for defenders. My focus is on translating real-world attack
		techniques into practical detections, investigation playbooks, and defensive guidance
		that security practitioners can apply in production environments.
	</p>
	<h3>Current Areas of Interest</h3>
	<ul>
		<li>Cloud Detection Engineering (AWS, Azure, and GCP)</li>
		<li>Identity Security and Identity Compromise</li>
		<li>AI-Assisted Detection Engineering</li>
		<li>Security Engineering &amp; Automation</li>
		<li>Incident Response Playbooks</li>
		<li>Threat Hunting</li>
	</ul>
	<h3>Certifications</h3>
	<ul>
		<li>GIAC Certified Forensic Analyst (GCFA)</li>
		<li>Certified Information Systems Security Professional (CISSP)</li>
		<li>CompTIA Advanced Security Practitioner (CASP+)</li>
		<li>AWS Security</li>
		<li>GCP Professional Security Operations Engineer</li>
	</ul>
	<p>
		Everything published on HeathBarSec is intended to be practical, reproducible,
		and focused on improving defensive capabilities through hands-on research and
		experimentation.
	</p>
</section>
</Layout>
